<br>
The answer is yes. Indeed I had wondered why it had not been posted before..likely people did not want it posted. Using the following method, you can level well from 51 through 54 (I stopped at 53 to move on to something else). Read well my dark elf bretheren.<br>
<br>
The prey are our hated shorties, the dwarves of Butcherblock. Specifically the dwarven guards. These guards are level 41ish (except for 2 which are 45..dont attack these) and are all warriors (no spells to worry about). They hate us...but they hate our pets more and stick to them like glue. A BO3 and DS lev 51 earth can SOLO these with about 20% - 40% health remaining UNLESS they are duel wielding. If you find a Dwarf who is duel wielding you will need to Chain cast pet once.<br>
<br>
Also of note they have HUGE MR. Dont bother casting spells on them repeatedly..they wont work. Dont bother malaise line spells..they wont hold. Also, they have a MINIMAL if no agro range. One can split a dwarf pair if they are 5 feet from eachother. If you ever get 2 dwarves send in pet and gate away to return for another try. Repop time is 30 min. There are up to 6 to 8 guards for you to kill. These guards are not the uber newbie guards transformed a while back.<br>
<br>
This protocol worked well for me. I killed 4 dwarves in a cycle (I couldnt kill any more without clarity in a spawn cycle. With clarity you can try for 6 or <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . The 4 guards will give you 1 blue bulb an hour in lev 52 (more in 51) IF done correctly. I hunted 1 guardhouse away from crossroads and 2 guardhouses from crossroads (2 guards at each house). I did not hunt at the crossroads guardhouse cause too many newbies lives depend on it. These chosen  guardhouses are not used too often (but they are used, so help out your fellow players in need when able) <br>
<br>
 Make a lev 51 pet a fair distance from the guardhouse (important, any 51 pet will solo a non duel wielding guard...no 51 pet (even a 58 hitter) will solo a duelwielding guard (one Chain cast is required). So just make a pet and let it be. Burn out 3, dam shield and  Pull with your lev 1 or 4 burn spell. Only one guard will come. Let pet have at him. Sit, med, reflect, write a sonnet. Eventually the guard will get to 20% health and will begin to walk away. Stand and watch health bar closely. Once his bar is about 10% health reclaim whatever is left of your pet and Nuke once. You get full XP, of a lev 41 guard, in a newbie zone (bonus). I used char, you can use your lev 44 SOS as well. Remember the High MR, so expect an occasional full or major resist and you may need to nuke again.<br>
<br>
You faction goes down with dwarves (go figure) but if your like me, you are already KOS. When done correctly it is an acceptable evil alternative to hunting your own in 3rd gate. And they make great sandwiches.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps anyone who doesnt wish to kill dark elves (leaves a bad taste in my mouth). I encourage anyone else who has similar strategies to come out of the closet and post them ..or at least email to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (fpe@po.cwru.edu)<br>
<br>
Good killing to you all<br>
Czzarre Llyncu<br>
53rd mage of Prexus<br>
