<br>
 Minor benifits to the guards not listed above..<br>
<br>
I feel that the guard killing does give more excitement. Its not much work, but you do need to keep an eye on you and the guard.<br>
<br>
The loot is about 5 to 10 plat pet kill. Each dwarf has up to 6 plat in coin. Every guard has a dwarven axe. hese axes are 2/26 1hs. Sell for 4 to 5 plat at vendors (depending on cha). Great for giving to newbies. Also they occasionally drop Fine steel and small bronze armor. this is a good area for our weightless bags. <br>
<br>
The newbies are around. This is both benifit and curse. It is always nice when newbies visit and gack in awe. many requests come up for mage summoned items (which is a plus in my book). I also throw free dam shields on many which is much enjoyd by that population. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp On the downside many a DrOOd has stopped and said &quot;I wanna loot&quot; or &quot;Got Lewt for me&quot; or &quot;I need 10K plat, give it to me&quot;. Unfortuatly sicking my pet on them is disallowed on my server.<br>
<br>
Another benifit is that a vendor will sell to you in the same zone. At the druid rings the spell vendor there sells to me (dont know why). So this cuts downtime allowing me to collect the coin. If anything its the coin that accumulates that sends me to the bank (I use the overthere hammer to port to Overthere bank for supplies and depositing coin).<br>
<br>
I appreciate the offer of Cyndreela. Any Others? Let em out. there are more tha 2 places for lev 51-54ish solos.<br>
<br>
